# Test fixtures for the CommonTraceFormat library.
#
# The CTF data-stream files (dummystream*, mychan_*, kernel_channel_*, chan*,
# stream*, u_*, *.mctf, ...) and the LTTng .idx index files are binary trace
# data. Mark everything under data/ as binary by default: Git then stores it
# verbatim (no end-of-line or encoding conversion) and the Qt sanity bot skips
# its text/UTF-8/EOL checks on it. This clears the blocking "Invalid UTF-8 in
# diff" and "CRLF line endings" sanity errors. (The remaining "big file" hits
# are non-blocking warnings; .gitattributes cannot change a file's size.)
data/**            binary

# The metadata fragments are text and worth diffing during review, but their
# bytes must be preserved exactly: some fixtures intentionally use CRLF or LF
# to exercise the parser. Keep them diffable while disabling EOL normalization.
data/**/metadata   -text diff
data/**/*.json     -text diff

# Plain-text helper fixtures.
data/**/README     text
data/**/*.expect   -text diff
